cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with sampling from distributions in challenging high-dimensional and non-convex statistics and machine learning applications. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with optimization problems in machine learning. Additionally, it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the analysis of the Metropolis acceptance probability of the algorithm. It could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it involves the analysis of numerical algorithms. Finally, it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the analysis of a stochastic system.
